Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine buff; grey core. Triangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 110, 33? A fairly common stamp attributed to the Nikandros group by Lawall
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1550)
